WEBVTT

00:23.648 --> 00:25.066
So, you ready?

00:26.526 --> 00:27.777
I'm ready.

00:28.987 --> 00:30.155
Big day is coming.

00:30.780 --> 00:33.825
Jury is a mixed bag
but we only need a few of them,

00:33.908 --> 00:38.872
probably women, who either love me,
impossible not to, or sympathize with you.

00:38.955 --> 00:40.957
With what you're trying
to build and accomplish.

00:41.041 --> 00:42.500
If not your path for getting there.

00:42.584 --> 00:44.002
What's our strategy?

00:44.085 --> 00:46.504
This whole shebang hangs on two words,

00:47.088 --> 00:48.631
dangerously close.

00:48.715 --> 00:53.094
When the judge gives the jury instructions
for deliberating on the crime of intent,

00:53.178 --> 00:56.598
that's the definition she'll enforce
upon them for reaching their verdict.

00:56.681 --> 00:58.349
She's going to ask them to decide

00:58.433 --> 01:01.269
if you were dangerously close
to committing a crime.

01:01.352 --> 01:03.271
Now, the lesser charges.

01:03.354 --> 01:08.151
The Beekman Hotel, the plane you borrowed,
we're fucked, there's too much evidence.

01:08.234 --> 01:09.611
The only way out of that is

01:09.694 --> 01:12.072
if the entire jury
falls madly in love with you.

01:12.155 --> 01:18.328
But Fortress, City National,
and Rachel fucking Williams,

01:18.411 --> 01:20.330
the big ones, we have a shot.

01:21.372 --> 01:22.665
We can strongly argue

01:22.749 --> 01:26.211
you were never dangerously close
to committing any of those crimes.

01:27.128 --> 01:29.506
So you're arguing I'm incompetent.

01:29.589 --> 01:31.925
At being a criminal mastermind?

01:32.008 --> 01:33.927
Yeah. That is my job.

01:34.010 --> 01:35.386
I was building a business.

01:35.470 --> 01:37.222
And that'll be part of my argument,

01:37.305 --> 01:41.184
but this isn't a business school final,
this is your actual freedom at stake.

01:41.267 --> 01:43.937
So I have to prove to them
that you were nowhere near

01:44.020 --> 01:46.940
getting any of that money
for your foundation. Okay?

01:47.816 --> 01:49.109
Okay.

01:49.192 --> 01:50.318
Any more questions?

01:50.401 --> 01:52.445
-What am I wearing?
-I don't give a fuck.

01:53.071 --> 01:55.615
I mean, the court supplies clothes.

01:55.698 --> 01:57.242
Simple but…

01:57.325 --> 01:58.868
I have a brand to consider.

01:58.952 --> 02:02.247
Also, it's different for women.
Do I need to explain this to you?

02:02.330 --> 02:04.749
-Just get me a stylist.
-You're nervous.

02:05.542 --> 02:08.044
Things feel out of your control.
I get this a lot.

02:08.128 --> 02:10.755
Best thing to do
is to look humble, wear the court clothes,

02:10.839 --> 02:12.257
let me do my song and dance

02:12.340 --> 02:15.635
about what a young,
well-meaning, little go-getter you are,

02:15.718 --> 02:17.345
and we have a chance…

02:18.346 --> 02:21.474
to convince these poor bastards
that are stuck with jury duty

02:21.558 --> 02:25.436
that you weren't dangerously close
to ripping off Rachel or these banks.

02:25.520 --> 02:26.938
Okay?

02:42.370 --> 02:44.080
<i>Danke.</i> Code.

02:46.666 --> 02:49.043
Uh-uh. You said two Cup Noodles
for ten minutes.

02:49.127 --> 02:51.963
Bring me 20 more minutes
and I'll give you four. Now go.

03:02.557 --> 03:03.850
And spread the word!

03:06.269 --> 03:07.312
Yo.

03:07.395 --> 03:08.521
Yo, yo-self.

03:08.605 --> 03:10.899
Who's your stylist hookup
who does rappers?

03:10.982 --> 03:11.941
-Natasha.
-Yeah.

03:12.025 --> 03:14.110
Oh, you thinking trial styles…

03:14.194 --> 03:18.448
I'm thinking like HBIC,
but also like young and coquette.

03:18.531 --> 03:21.576
Mmm-hmm. Like <i>Lolita</i>
meets <i>Mildred Pierce</i> but like now.

03:21.659 --> 03:22.785
You got the funds?

03:22.869 --> 03:24.245
You know I got that Daddy paper.

03:24.329 --> 03:27.415
Just because you're inside
doesn't mean you can slang it up.

03:27.498 --> 03:30.919
-Just make the connect, I'll call back.
-You mean holla back?

03:35.173 --> 03:37.091
-You okay?
-Yeah, why?

03:38.509 --> 03:40.845
You gotta send a warning text
before you call a bitch.

03:40.929 --> 03:43.806
Thought you got cancer,
or pregnant or some shit.

03:43.890 --> 03:45.016
No, I'm good,

03:45.099 --> 03:48.436
but I've got a friend in trouble,
on trial starting tomorrow.

03:48.519 --> 03:49.646
High profile…

03:49.729 --> 03:52.482
SoHo grifter? Yeah. I know.

03:52.565 --> 03:54.400
You down to style her?

03:54.484 --> 03:57.320
Hmm, so she can stiff me too? No thanks.

03:57.403 --> 03:59.322
-That's her, I'm gonna…

04:01.199 --> 04:03.618
Natasha, Anna. Anna--

04:03.701 --> 04:06.246
Natasha, hi!
Thank you so much for doing this.

04:06.329 --> 04:09.207
Look, my rate's 1,200 a day just to be…

04:09.290 --> 04:10.792
Yes! Yes. Of course.

04:10.875 --> 04:13.962
I'll get my father
to wire you the fee as soon as we start.

04:14.045 --> 04:16.130
Cool, cool, so what's the vibe?

04:16.214 --> 04:20.385
So, the photos from this trial
are going to live forever.

04:20.468 --> 04:24.555
They may actually define
my entire identity going forward so…

04:24.639 --> 04:26.099
So no pressure.

04:26.182 --> 04:27.225
Okay, I gotta drop.

04:27.308 --> 04:29.227
Okay. I got you.

04:29.310 --> 04:32.146
Let's stay classic with a modern touch.

04:32.814 --> 04:36.067
Profesh, with a young, bohemian edge.

04:36.150 --> 04:38.695
Perfect. The photographers
will be behind me

04:38.778 --> 04:42.407
for most of the trial so the backs
shouldn't be an afterthought.

04:42.490 --> 04:44.492
With me? Never.

04:44.575 --> 04:46.786
Gosh, the lighting in there.

04:47.537 --> 04:51.457
Wicked fluorescent overheads,
a strong silhouette can conquer all.

04:52.458 --> 04:53.835
Don't worry.

04:54.627 --> 04:55.670
I got you, Anna.

04:56.629 --> 04:57.714
Thank you.

05:03.511 --> 05:04.554
Here.

05:10.226 --> 05:12.395
Vivian. How are you?

05:12.478 --> 05:13.438
Um…

05:13.521 --> 05:15.773
So, uh, who else is covering my trial?

05:15.857 --> 05:18.526
How would I know? <i>The Post,</i> probably.

05:18.609 --> 05:21.070
<i>The Post,</i> obviously,
but what about <i>The Times?</i>

05:21.154 --> 05:23.239
<i>The Times? The New York Times?</i>

05:23.323 --> 05:24.657
Or the networks?

05:24.741 --> 05:27.535
I don't know how national
the interest is in this case.

05:27.618 --> 05:29.746
But you could make them interested.

05:29.829 --> 05:32.248
I'm reporting on the trial,
not promoting it.

05:32.332 --> 05:34.500
More coverage benefits you too, no?

05:34.584 --> 05:35.585
-Anna…

05:35.668 --> 05:36.919
Validates your reporting,

05:37.003 --> 05:39.964
unless you're happy
with it just being a local story.

05:40.048 --> 05:42.675
-Don't you want bragging rights?
-I'm hanging up now.

05:42.759 --> 05:46.721
You know, you should also profile Rachel,
show what a shady-ass scammer she is.

05:46.804 --> 05:47.972
Goodbye, Anna.

05:56.397 --> 05:57.648
Spodek and Associates.

05:57.732 --> 05:58.858
Todd, now.

05:59.817 --> 06:02.153
Uh, I'm afraid
he's not in right now, Anna.

06:02.236 --> 06:04.155
You're lying, Alexi.

06:04.238 --> 06:06.157
Would you like to leave a message?

06:07.784 --> 06:11.913
You know, I've met a lot
of colorful characters in here.

06:11.996 --> 06:14.582
Murderers, hitwomen,

06:14.665 --> 06:18.753
you know, I had no idea how cheap
it was to have someone killed. Did you?

06:18.836 --> 06:22.298
Like, seriously,
like the price of a knock-off Chanel bag.

06:22.382 --> 06:23.549
Can you believe it?

06:23.633 --> 06:25.426
Uh, would you like to leave a message?

06:25.510 --> 06:27.887
Tell Todd to call my father.

06:27.970 --> 06:31.724
Have him either
wire ten grand to pay my stylist

06:32.725 --> 06:34.727
or bring it when he comes for the trial.

06:34.811 --> 06:35.895
I will let him know.

06:35.978 --> 06:39.565
Oh. And, Alexi, don't lie next time.

06:51.661 --> 06:53.871
There's a little bit of Anna in all of us.

06:55.123 --> 06:56.999
Everyone lies a little bit.

06:57.083 --> 07:01.337
We are all, every one of us, inside…

07:06.217 --> 07:08.928
There's a little bit of Anna in all of us.

07:09.011 --> 07:10.138
Not me.

07:11.097 --> 07:15.143
Maybe you pad your resumé,
exaggerate on your sales pitch,

07:15.226 --> 07:17.728
toy with the filters on your social media.

07:17.812 --> 07:19.355
-Guilty.
-We all do it.

07:20.148 --> 07:22.817
Every one of us has become a brand,

07:22.900 --> 07:26.279
an image,
a lie we project out into the world.

07:26.362 --> 07:27.196
Ugh.

07:27.280 --> 07:28.990
-What?
-Nothing.

07:29.657 --> 07:31.534
-Is it good?
-Very.

07:31.617 --> 07:33.786
-Then what?
-Then what, what?

07:33.870 --> 07:37.498
Validate me. Criticize me, help me,
anything but withhold from me.

07:37.582 --> 07:40.543
-She's lucky to have you.
-She is, right?

07:42.879 --> 07:45.173
Did you just double entendre me?

07:45.256 --> 07:47.383
Have me? Do you think she owns me?

07:48.426 --> 07:49.886
-Come on, Mags.
-I just…

07:50.636 --> 07:53.890
I want to fast forward to spring break.

07:53.973 --> 07:57.310
I want sand in my toes
and margaritas in both hands.

07:57.393 --> 08:00.396
I want a family chicken fight
in the shallow end of the heated pool,

08:00.480 --> 08:02.982
and I want this trial behind us.

08:03.065 --> 08:05.318
-I want that too.

08:05.401 --> 08:07.236
Do you think that I don't want that?

08:08.404 --> 08:09.697
Oh, fuck me.

08:13.117 --> 08:15.536
Jury's going to love you. Knock 'em dead.

08:17.955 --> 08:18.873
Yeah.

08:19.624 --> 08:21.000
Yeah, no, I'm on my way.

08:51.197 --> 08:53.199
-Baxter.
-McCaw.

08:55.326 --> 08:56.160
Who's that?

08:57.537 --> 08:59.330
Eyes and ears. A proxy for Cy.

09:01.624 --> 09:03.251
The DA's taken an interest.

09:06.379 --> 09:08.172
Did I miss anything?

09:08.256 --> 09:10.383
-Still waiting.
-Where should I sit?

09:11.133 --> 09:13.135
Team Anna is this side.

09:13.219 --> 09:15.846
Team Rachel is that side.

09:15.930 --> 09:18.558
Neff, honey, I'm Switzerland in all this.

09:18.641 --> 09:22.186
-What do you mean she's not dressed?
-The defendant is in prison garb.

09:22.270 --> 09:24.188
What's the deal, Mr. Spodek?

09:24.272 --> 09:27.567
I'm not sure
what the issue is, Your Honor.

09:27.650 --> 09:30.403
-What did Natasha say?
-She texted, she dropped the clothes off.

09:30.486 --> 09:32.655
-Why isn't she--
-Step off. Texting.

09:32.738 --> 09:34.365
In all my years,

09:34.448 --> 09:37.243
I've been held up
at gunpoint in this courtroom,

09:37.326 --> 09:38.869
but never over wardrobe.

09:38.953 --> 09:40.246
If you let me go speak--

09:40.329 --> 09:42.957
I believe the court provides
clothing for those in need.

09:43.040 --> 09:44.292
Yes. I'm aware.

09:44.375 --> 09:47.169
Another gold star
for your report card, Counselor.

09:47.253 --> 09:48.838
The defendant won't wear them.

09:48.921 --> 09:52.091
I'm going to sip
this iced coffee, Mr. Spodek,

09:52.174 --> 09:53.509
and when I'm finished,

09:53.593 --> 09:57.013
if your client
isn't dressed and before me,

09:57.096 --> 10:00.349
I'm going to be wildly, deeply unhappy.

10:01.100 --> 10:02.310
Yes, Your Honor.

10:02.393 --> 10:05.605
And don't let the jumbo size fool you.

10:05.688 --> 10:07.106
I drink fast.

10:09.775 --> 10:13.571
Get dressed.
We can't keep the court waiting.

10:13.654 --> 10:16.073
-This is insane.
-Those clothes are insane.

10:16.157 --> 10:17.783
I'd rather wear my jumpsuit.

10:17.867 --> 10:19.827
-You can't.
-Why not?

10:19.910 --> 10:22.496
Because first impressions
matter to jurors.

10:22.580 --> 10:25.041
You look way too comfortable
in a prison jumpsuit.

10:25.124 --> 10:27.501
And the judge won't allow it.
It is legally not allowed.

10:27.585 --> 10:30.338
It's a bad look in our courtroom
and could lead to a mistrial.

10:30.421 --> 10:33.174
You're making an enemy of her on day one.

10:33.257 --> 10:34.842
Every second that we delay--

10:34.925 --> 10:36.844
Then get me clothes I can wear.

10:39.889 --> 10:42.975
Put the fucking clothes on.
This is hurting you, Anna.

10:43.059 --> 10:46.103
Hurting me? I'm fine.

10:50.983 --> 10:53.194
-Tell her to wear the court clothes.
-I did.

10:53.277 --> 10:55.905
She looked at me
like I asked to fuck her in the ass.

10:55.988 --> 10:59.325
-Where are the clothes?
-Rikers. She dropped them off last night.

10:59.408 --> 11:01.410
-She have others?
-I can't reach--

11:01.494 --> 11:03.329
-Get them here.
-I can't reach her.

11:03.412 --> 11:05.915
-I think she's crashed out after--
-Wake her up.

11:05.998 --> 11:08.125
I do not work for you.

11:08.918 --> 11:10.836
This is so fucked.

11:10.920 --> 11:14.965
We've got 30 minutes before this judge
loses her fucking shit on me.

11:15.049 --> 11:16.842
-You'd better get shopping.
-Me?

11:16.926 --> 11:18.719
Y'all figure it out, I got a shift.

11:18.803 --> 11:22.807
Okay, this is… I'm in court,
I can't leave to go shopping.

11:22.890 --> 11:25.142
I can't participate in Anna's defense!

11:25.226 --> 11:28.604
That would be unethical,
crossing a line journalistically.

11:28.688 --> 11:30.106
Well, I'm a fucking guy.

11:30.189 --> 11:32.191
Can you tell me
what pantyhose or whatever--

11:32.274 --> 11:35.778
-Do you think pantyhose is going to be--
-What's wrong with that?

11:35.861 --> 11:37.154
Fine!

11:37.238 --> 11:41.033
But you will give me access
to all of the discovery in this case.

11:41.117 --> 11:45.287
Everything. Anna's phone, email,
everything the prosecution has, I want.

11:45.371 --> 11:47.915
Yes. Fuck. Whatever. Just go.

12:04.598 --> 12:07.935
-Hi, welcome to--
-Business, sweet, modest. Now.

12:08.018 --> 12:09.854
-They're right over there.
-Show me.

12:18.112 --> 12:20.531
Flats, black, size 7. Go!

12:41.844 --> 12:46.015
Vivian must have thought this was
a shoelace or a belt or something.

12:46.932 --> 12:48.309
A happy accident.

12:49.602 --> 12:52.563
But this is not
a great start for our team.

12:52.646 --> 12:55.316
I'm very underwhelmed
with our preparation on day one.

12:55.399 --> 12:57.443
We have to go!

12:58.778 --> 13:00.279
Now!

13:02.198 --> 13:04.533
Don't crowd my entrance.

14:28.117 --> 14:29.618
-You good?
-Mmm-hmm.

14:30.911 --> 14:34.039
Thank you so very much
for joining us, Miss Sorokin.

14:34.123 --> 14:36.083
Officer, bring in the jury.

14:37.918 --> 14:40.462
On October 11th, 1944,

14:40.546 --> 14:44.925
Frank Sinatra opened
the Paramount Theater in Times Square.

14:45.009 --> 14:48.929
Women swooned
at the sight of <i>Ol' Blue Eyes.</i>

14:49.013 --> 14:50.472
They literally fainted.

14:50.556 --> 14:53.475
To the public,
this was the Sinatra effect,

14:53.559 --> 14:59.273
but in reality, it was strategically
created by Sinatra's press agents.

15:00.274 --> 15:02.192
Women were paid to swoon.

15:02.276 --> 15:05.070
And plant kisses,
and throw their clothes on stage.

15:05.154 --> 15:08.657
Ambulances and nurses were stationed
outside the theater on purpose.

15:08.741 --> 15:12.161
All because if he can make it here…

15:13.787 --> 15:14.955
he'll make it anywhere.

15:16.248 --> 15:18.918
Anna came to New York
just like some of you did.

15:19.001 --> 15:22.504
Bright-eyed and bushy-tailed,
excited by the opportunities.

15:22.588 --> 15:24.798
A mere 25 years old.

15:24.882 --> 15:27.301
No rich parents. No connections.

15:27.384 --> 15:29.345
No fancy school pedigree.

15:29.428 --> 15:31.597
Anna couldn't
wait around for opportunities.

15:31.680 --> 15:34.391
She had to create them.
We can all relate to that.

15:34.475 --> 15:37.227
There's a little bit of Anna in all of us.

15:37.895 --> 15:40.731
Everyone lies a little bit.

15:40.814 --> 15:44.777
Whether it's on a resumé,
or a sales pitch, or on social media.

15:44.860 --> 15:46.987
We think the world
has changed with social media.

15:47.071 --> 15:49.448
Every person has become a brand.

15:49.531 --> 15:52.868
An image fed out into the world. A lie.

15:53.786 --> 15:57.414
But what was true
for Anna was true for Sinatra.

15:57.498 --> 16:00.209
Sometimes you've gotta
fake it till you make it.

16:00.292 --> 16:06.757
So, Anna followed suit
and became the person she wanted to be.

16:06.840 --> 16:10.719
A person who would receive
the red carpet from New York's elite.

16:10.803 --> 16:14.014
She allowed everyone to believe
the story they wanted to believe.

16:14.098 --> 16:16.016
It wasn't a crime when Sinatra did it.

16:16.767 --> 16:18.435
It isn't a crime now.

16:19.311 --> 16:20.813
The people you'll hear from,

16:20.896 --> 16:23.524
they wanted to believe
that Anna was a German heiress

16:23.607 --> 16:25.859
because it benefited them to do so.

16:25.943 --> 16:27.027
That's what they got.

16:27.111 --> 16:31.699
Not for one single moment did Anna
have the intent of stealing any money.

16:31.782 --> 16:34.451
Every person that walks in here

16:34.535 --> 16:37.579
and sits in that chair
wanted to give Anna money

16:37.663 --> 16:41.291
because they wanted
to be in business with her.

16:41.375 --> 16:43.961
To be close to Anna Delvey!

16:44.753 --> 16:46.296
The German heiress!

16:46.380 --> 16:49.425
Would they have wanted to be
in business with Anna Sorokin?

16:50.092 --> 16:52.845
A middle class foreigner? No.

16:52.928 --> 16:57.224
Anna had to fake it till she made it.

16:57.891 --> 16:59.518
You may judge her for that.

16:59.601 --> 17:00.728
Find her unethical.

17:00.811 --> 17:03.063
Like some would find Sinatra unethical

17:03.147 --> 17:05.357
for staging fainting women
at his performances.

17:05.441 --> 17:10.237
But it is not illegal.

17:11.155 --> 17:14.450
And the truth is,
what you need to remember most of all…

17:15.951 --> 17:20.039
the evidence will show you
that Anna was never close,

17:20.122 --> 17:24.084
let alone dangerously close
to getting these loans

17:24.168 --> 17:28.172
or stealing from anyone who gets
in that chair and tells you otherwise.

17:28.255 --> 17:30.966
Not. One. Dollar.

17:35.345 --> 17:36.346
Thank you.

17:41.602 --> 17:44.063
The Sinatra defense. Bold.

17:46.106 --> 17:48.233
One last administrative issue, Your Honor.

17:48.317 --> 17:50.444
At a later date, we will put into evidence

17:50.527 --> 17:53.113
the contents
of the defendant's cellphone and laptop

17:53.197 --> 17:55.282
as we anticipated communication

17:55.365 --> 17:57.910
between the defendant
and her various contacts.

17:57.993 --> 18:00.954
I wanted to alert you
that there have been technical issues

18:01.038 --> 18:03.373
with our IT department
due to a computer crash.

18:03.457 --> 18:06.376
And, you know, the major thing
is that most of our exhibits

18:06.460 --> 18:08.921
are in a state
where they would be presentable,

18:09.004 --> 18:12.091
the only issue that persists,
and we made it a high priority…

18:12.800 --> 18:15.260
-What's she--
-I'll ask Todd.

18:15.344 --> 18:19.306
There are two witnesses who
would testify relating to those matters.

18:24.770 --> 18:27.189
-What's wrong?
-Where is everyone?

18:31.527 --> 18:33.403
She wants to know where everyone is.

18:34.655 --> 18:36.323
Everyone? Who's everyone?

18:37.658 --> 18:38.659
The press?

18:38.742 --> 18:40.410
Her public? Whatever.

18:48.919 --> 18:50.838
Only press can take pictures in here.

18:51.839 --> 18:54.591
-You're press, you take it then.
-What's this for?

18:56.385 --> 18:59.763
I'm gonna light this whole scene
up in here. Watch me.

18:59.847 --> 19:03.392
See those photographers,
that's <i>Daily Mail, New York Post, AP.</i>

19:03.475 --> 19:06.270
They publish instantaneously.
You need pics, use theirs.

19:47.477 --> 19:48.979
The people call Alan Reed.

19:50.772 --> 19:52.316
And did you provide your services

19:52.399 --> 19:55.027
connecting her
with banks who might extend a loan?

19:55.110 --> 19:57.946
-I did.
