For me.

37:53.604 --> 37:54.689
And because I can.

37:56.399 --> 37:57.775
I'm fucking down to fight.

38:03.406 --> 38:05.074
But you need to stop fighting me.

38:13.124 --> 38:18.129
I would rather go to jail forever
then come off like some wannabe.

38:19.088 --> 38:20.673
Some amateur.

38:21.257 --> 38:26.595
Some lazy millennial just looking
for a shortcut to fame and fortune.

38:26.679 --> 38:28.139
Yeah. Some Rachel.

38:31.017 --> 38:34.603
I want respect.

38:35.604 --> 38:37.898
I want you to defend me out there.

38:37.982 --> 38:42.945
I want you to defend my work,
my foundation. My achievements.

38:46.032 --> 38:47.074
My father…

38:49.201 --> 38:51.078
everyone, everyone,

38:52.121 --> 38:55.082
they have to know how close I was.

38:55.166 --> 38:59.754
They have to know that I'm not a fraud.

39:03.049 --> 39:04.216
You have my word.

39:05.968 --> 39:06.802
Get dressed.

39:14.643 --> 39:16.812
This is unacceptable
and inappropriate.

39:16.896 --> 39:19.231
I have had a jury here since 9:30.

39:19.315 --> 39:21.484
You are on trial in a criminal court.

39:21.567 --> 39:23.402
This is not a fashion show.

39:23.486 --> 39:25.488
Who in the hell do you think you are?

39:25.571 --> 39:27.073
I apologize, Your Honor.

39:27.156 --> 39:28.741
Next time, the officers will

39:28.824 --> 39:31.202
wrap you in drapes
and drag you to that chair.

39:31.285 --> 39:35.081
-You understand, Miss Sorokin?
-Yes, Your Honor.

39:35.164 --> 39:38.125
-Okay. Let's bring in the jury.

39:38.209 --> 39:41.003
We learned a lot about
your bio from your testimony.

39:41.087 --> 39:43.172
Good upbringing, good college.

39:43.255 --> 39:46.342
Landing your dream job
three months after arriving here.

39:46.425 --> 39:47.259
Wow.

39:47.343 --> 39:49.220
Congratulations on your
success as a writer.

39:49.303 --> 39:51.847
-It's enviable. We should all be so lucky.
-Objection.

39:52.515 --> 39:54.767
Ask a question, Mr. Spodek.

39:55.559 --> 39:58.062
Were you familiar
with Anna before meeting her?

39:58.729 --> 40:00.064
I saw her on social media.

40:00.147 --> 40:02.400
So fair to say you wanted
to meet her before you did.

40:02.483 --> 40:05.611
She was interesting.
Her feed was interesting to me, yes.

40:05.694 --> 40:08.406
What was interesting about her?
Or her social media feeds?

40:09.198 --> 40:11.450
Photos of art, travel,

40:11.534 --> 40:13.911
the editor-in-chief,
I guess, at <i>Purple Magazine.</i>

40:13.994 --> 40:15.788
So similar careers attracted you?

40:15.871 --> 40:18.666
Both working in fashion magazines.
Anna maybe had a leg up but--

40:18.749 --> 40:19.583
Yes.

40:20.209 --> 40:24.213
And when you did become friends with Anna,
did you ever pay for a drink?

40:24.296 --> 40:26.382
-She wouldn't let me--
-Answer the question.

40:28.759 --> 40:29.969
Not that I recall.

40:30.052 --> 40:34.348
Any of the dozens of dinners at Le Coucou
and other fine dining establishments?

40:34.432 --> 40:37.184
-Not that I recall.
-Spa treatments? Facials?

40:37.268 --> 40:39.812
Infrared saunas? Massages, nail salons?

40:39.895 --> 40:43.732
-No. Anna was very generous.
-Celebrity personal training sessions?

40:43.816 --> 40:45.651
-No.
-You never paid for any of them?

40:46.944 --> 40:49.738
And how many of these various luxuries

40:49.822 --> 40:52.908
did Anna buy for you
over the two years you hung out together?

40:52.992 --> 40:55.536
-Like what?
-Start with dinners and go from there.

40:56.328 --> 40:57.455
How many?

40:59.331 --> 41:01.375
-I don't recall.
-You didn't write them down?

41:01.459 --> 41:03.919
-No.
-How will you remember them for your book?

41:04.003 --> 41:06.338
-Objection, Your Honor.
-Sustained.

41:07.590 --> 41:10.718
Did you cooperate with the NYPD,

41:10.801 --> 41:15.014
with a detective to aid in the arrest
of your friend, Anna Sorokin?

41:18.893 --> 41:19.977
Yes. It was the only way--

41:20.060 --> 41:23.397
Why didn't you mention that
in your account in <i>Vanity Fair?</i>

41:23.481 --> 41:24.940
I didn't have enough space.

41:25.024 --> 41:26.734
But of all the details.

41:26.817 --> 41:28.777
You wrote about hitting the town together

41:28.861 --> 41:32.448
and nice little bonding moments
you had with Anna with beautiful detail.

41:32.531 --> 41:36.202
You didn't think the dramatic event
of setting up a sting operation

41:36.285 --> 41:39.830
to arrest Anna was worthy
of space in your article?

41:40.789 --> 41:42.166
I didn't have enough space.

41:42.249 --> 41:43.209
Mmm.

41:43.292 --> 41:45.085
How much are you being paid

41:45.169 --> 41:47.963
to write a book
about your experience with Anna?

41:49.089 --> 41:51.800
I don't know.
I don't really understand how contracts--

41:51.884 --> 41:54.428
I'm an attorney, so let me help you out.

41:56.096 --> 42:01.185
It says here you get 300 grand spread out
over four payments. Sound about right?

42:01.268 --> 42:02.102
Yes.

42:02.186 --> 42:04.772
And your TV deal, do you know
how much you're getting for that?

42:04.855 --> 42:08.943
-Or do you need help explaining it?
-I think it's around… 30,000.

42:09.026 --> 42:13.113
For the option. And then another $300,000
if the show gets made. Correct?

42:13.781 --> 42:18.035
-Correct.
-So in total, $630,000.

42:18.118 --> 42:21.288
Plus the 1,200 you got from <i>Vanity Fair</i>
for writing the article. Correct?

42:21.372 --> 42:24.625
I don't want my testimony
to be misconstrued or seen

42:24.708 --> 42:27.253
as a ploy for my own benefit
because it's not.

42:27.336 --> 42:30.673
It's not about entertainment,
it's about law and order and a crime!

42:30.756 --> 42:32.466
For you it is about entertainment, right?

42:32.550 --> 42:37.555
This is about trauma, the judicial system
in America, warning others so…

42:37.638 --> 42:38.973
This is not about entertainment,

42:39.056 --> 42:42.184
this is the most traumatic thing
that I have ever been through.

42:42.268 --> 42:43.561
I understand all that.

42:43.644 --> 42:46.855
But this traumatic experience
that you went through,

42:46.939 --> 42:49.942
you sold to three separate people. Right?

42:56.699 --> 42:57.658
I worked very hard.

42:57.741 --> 42:58.867
Answer the question.

43:01.829 --> 43:05.499
Yes, I did sell to three separate people,
but I worked very hard.

43:05.583 --> 43:07.710
And when you say
you worked very hard,

43:07.793 --> 43:10.546
you worked very hard
on befriending Miss Sorokin,

43:10.629 --> 43:12.798
by benefitting from her connections,

43:12.881 --> 43:14.258
her extreme generosity,

43:14.341 --> 43:17.678
and after one thing
that doesn't go your way, one mishap,

43:17.761 --> 43:22.850
you worked very hard on cooperating
with the police to have Anna arrested.

43:22.933 --> 43:27.104
You worked very hard on luring her
out of her rehab center in Malibu,

43:27.187 --> 43:29.189
pretending to be meeting her for lunch.

43:29.273 --> 43:33.360
You worked very hard
on your dream of becoming a writer

43:33.444 --> 43:35.821
by finding a character
and creating as juicy a story--

43:35.904 --> 43:37.489
-Objection.
-Overruled.

43:37.573 --> 43:38.449
No. This is…

43:38.532 --> 43:42.202
And you worked very hard
on selling that story

43:42.286 --> 43:46.040
of your experience with Anna
to the highest bidders, right?

43:49.835 --> 43:51.295
This is not…

43:52.004 --> 43:53.881
I wish I'd never met Anna.

43:53.964 --> 43:56.383
I wouldn't wish this on anybody.

43:56.467 --> 43:58.469
This is the worst thing
that's ever happened to me.

43:58.552 --> 44:02.056
Two years after arriving
to this city to make it as a writer,

44:02.139 --> 44:04.433
you've published
an article in <i>Vanity Fair.</i>

44:04.516 --> 44:08.395
You have over $600,000 in book
and TV deals coming your way.

44:08.479 --> 44:13.484
All because you found and befriended
and turned Anna in to the police.

44:13.567 --> 44:15.611
If this is the worst thing
that happened to you,

44:15.694 --> 44:17.279
-we should all be so lucky.
-Objection.

44:17.363 --> 44:19.531
Withdrawn.
No further questions, Your Honor.

44:42.096 --> 44:43.597
You dropped a dime on Anna?

44:46.350 --> 44:49.728
Worked with the cops?
Set her up? Lured her out of rehab?

44:49.812 --> 44:51.105
Look, I can explain.

44:52.314 --> 44:54.650
-I know you're probably angry--
-This is shock.

44:55.359 --> 44:56.860
You'll know when I'm angry.

44:56.944 --> 45:00.614
I had to cooperate with the police.
It was the only way to get reimbursed.

45:00.698 --> 45:01.699
Why hide it?

45:04.034 --> 45:05.327
I was ashamed.

45:06.370 --> 45:07.579
I felt used.

45:08.247 --> 45:09.790
By the police, by the prosecutor--

45:09.873 --> 45:12.751
I feel used.

45:12.835 --> 45:14.086
By you.

45:14.169 --> 45:17.089
Thinking you're some kind of victim
in all this. Taking care of you.

45:17.172 --> 45:19.758
I am a victim in all of this.

45:19.842 --> 45:22.344
At least you'll get to cry
into all that money.

45:22.428 --> 45:26.974
Looks like you'll have plenty left over,
even after you pay Amex that 60K you owe.

45:29.351 --> 45:32.062
Unless someone
already paid that back for you.

45:34.022 --> 45:36.191
Do not withhold
from me in this moment or--

45:36.275 --> 45:39.278
Amex took care of it. They saw how crazy
this situation was and they--

45:39.361 --> 45:43.407
So you made out just fine
from dropping a dime on your friend!

45:57.212 --> 45:58.797
-Is that…
-Yeah.

45:58.881 --> 46:00.048
-Are you going to--
-No.

46:00.549 --> 46:01.633
Okay.

46:02.593 --> 46:05.137
-But what if it's--
-Lines. Boundaries.

46:06.555 --> 46:12.311
Cheers to…
your excellent cross of Rachel today.

46:12.394 --> 46:15.564
Could help with one charge,
but the other nine…

46:16.648 --> 46:19.902
Oh, Catherine's like
this unstoppable fact robot,

46:19.985 --> 46:22.070
shoveling her evidence
down their captive throats

46:22.154 --> 46:25.157
until they're so fucking full
there's no room for any of mine.

46:25.783 --> 46:27.367
So we shift strategy.

46:27.451 --> 46:28.869
Yeah, well, my best strategy

46:28.952 --> 46:32.206
that she was never dangerously close
to getting any of that money.

46:32.289 --> 46:34.249
I can't fucking use because my client

46:34.333 --> 46:36.543
would rather rot in jail
than allow strangers

46:36.627 --> 46:38.378
to think she's bad at business.

46:38.462 --> 46:42.049
-Who says you have to listen to her?
-Ethics. Decency.

46:42.132 --> 46:44.384
Whatever it takes, right?

46:45.511 --> 46:48.889
Come on.
You did great today. You got this!

46:48.972 --> 46:50.015
How drunk are you?

46:50.098 --> 46:54.186
I'm excited. We could win this puppy.

46:54.269 --> 46:58.232
Anna could be sitting right there,
on that stool, in a week's time.

47:00.526 --> 47:02.778
Anna would never be
caught dead in this place.

47:06.949 --> 47:07.950
We should go home.

47:08.700 --> 47:09.827
Probably should.

47:12.079 --> 47:12.913
Oh.

47:13.789 --> 47:17.042
Boundaries. Boundaries, Vivian.

47:19.586 --> 47:21.213
-Yes, I accept.

47:22.214 --> 47:23.799
What's up, Anna?

47:31.306 --> 47:33.350
You got a thing I don't know about?

47:33.433 --> 47:35.310
I thought you were asleep.

47:35.394 --> 47:36.228
I was.

47:37.062 --> 47:39.815
I keep thinking I'm hearing her cry.

47:39.898 --> 47:44.278
Then I wake up
and it's like ghost cries or something.

47:45.028 --> 47:45.988
Do you hear those too?

47:46.071 --> 47:48.866
What happened to all of my dresses?

47:48.949 --> 47:50.909
Fashion police
raided the place this afternoon.

47:50.993 --> 47:52.160
I should have told you.

47:52.244 --> 47:56.039
I have to get clothes to Rikers by 11:00
or they won't be there

47:56.123 --> 47:59.251
when they take her in the morning,
and it'll be another fiasco.

47:59.334 --> 48:03.547
Her? See, when I say "her,"
I mean our daughter. When you say "her--"

48:03.630 --> 48:05.924
It's just clothes, I'm just helping.

48:06.008 --> 48:07.217
Ah, there you are!

48:08.302 --> 48:12.139
If I showed a video of you
to college you right now,

48:12.222 --> 48:13.682
she would freak the fuck out.

48:13.765 --> 48:17.311
It's just a dress, Jack.
Why does this bother you so much?

48:17.394 --> 48:19.771
It's bothering me
that it's not bothering you.

48:19.855 --> 48:24.151
Of course it's bothering me.
I hate thinking about clothes.

48:24.234 --> 48:26.987
I hate being away from my daughter
and going to Rikers.

48:27.070 --> 48:28.280
Then why?

48:28.363 --> 48:30.699
Because I created this monster.

48:30.782 --> 48:33.410
Now the eyes of the world
are on her. She has no one.

48:33.493 --> 48:36.538
There are plenty of good reasons
why she has no one.

48:38.081 --> 48:40.334
I need to get this to Rikers, so…

48:42.210 --> 48:43.587
How can you even say this to me?

48:43.670 --> 48:46.006
For months, you have known
about this vacation!

48:46.089 --> 48:48.050
It's my fault
this trial is dragging on?

48:48.133 --> 48:51.845
-Nothing is your fault. How could it be?
-I can't just abandon my client!

48:51.929 --> 48:54.848
Handing off to co-counsel
is not abandonment.

48:54.932 --> 48:57.935
You haven't been there,
not once, to support me.

48:58.018 --> 49:01.563
You have no idea, with a shit-ton
of media attention, I can't just give up--

49:01.647 --> 49:04.024
-Now we know what this is really about.
-What?

49:04.107 --> 49:06.276
You wanna be there
for the press conference,

49:06.360 --> 49:08.654
so half a dozen
of your law school classmates

49:08.737 --> 49:10.697
can see your face on New York 1. Pathetic.

49:10.781 --> 49:13.700
-I could give a fuck--
-If this was a death row case, sure!

49:13.784 --> 49:16.912
Take all the time you need,
but your entire ego is riding

49:16.995 --> 49:20.540
on this spoiled little thief who is,
let us face it, guilty as all get-out!

49:20.624 --> 49:22.834
If she is a killer,
she wouldn't need me,

49:22.918 --> 49:24.294
but she's not. She's a kid.

49:24.378 --> 49:27.714
An immigrant kid, who came to this country
for the American dream--

49:27.798 --> 49:30.300
Please don't wrap the flag
around this psycho.

49:30.384 --> 49:32.094
I am all she has!

49:36.181 --> 49:39.059
You were raised on Mount fucking Olympus.

49:39.142 --> 49:41.645
You could never understand
what that's like.

49:42.729 --> 49:46.108
Please… explain it to me.

49:56.785 --> 49:58.787
-Get it, go on.
-No.

49:58.870 --> 50:00.998
Go tell Anna
how great she looked in court today.

50:01.957 --> 50:05.210
You act like I'm fucking this chick.
She's a client!

50:05.293 --> 50:07.921
I wish you were,
because it would help explain to me

50:08.005 --> 50:09.840
why you suddenly think it is okay

50:09.923 --> 50:13.218
to completely ruin
our only vacation in two years.

50:21.810 --> 50:24.062
-I have boundaries.
-She'll call again.

50:24.146 --> 50:25.063
Hello.

50:25.147 --> 50:28.358
Oh. Hi. Brian, right? Is your dad there?

50:28.442 --> 50:30.068
He's fighting with my mom.

50:30.152 --> 50:33.238
I can wait.
But not very long. I'm in jail.

50:33.321 --> 50:34.740
What did you do?

50:34.823 --> 50:37.117
Nothing, I just borrowed some money.

50:37.200 --> 50:38.827
And a jet.

50:38.910 --> 50:40.537
<i>Can I borrow some money?</i>

50:41.955 --> 50:43.415
Your dad has all my money.

50:43.498 --> 50:45.417
He won't give me any.

50:45.500 --> 50:46.460
<i>I doubt that.</i>

50:47.294 --> 50:48.420
He's a nice guy.

50:49.129 --> 50:50.714
And he loves you very much.

50:50.797 --> 50:53.300
But he's making my mom sad.

50:53.383 --> 50:55.510
<i>You can probably blame me for that.</i>

50:55.594 --> 50:58.930
<i>But you can also use that</i>
<i>to get what you want.</i>

50:59.014 --> 51:00.223
I can?

51:00.307 --> 51:04.311
Sure. People give people money
for all sorts of reasons.

51:04.394 --> 51:07.814
Guilt and love are two of the biggest.

51:07.898 --> 51:11.401
And you've got both.
You should ask for the moon.

51:12.110 --> 51:13.445
I'll go get my dad.

51:13.528 --> 51:17.365
No, don't. Let them fight.

51:17.449 --> 51:20.243
But I don't like it. It's loud.

51:21.119 --> 51:22.704
It's better than silence.

51:26.249 --> 51:29.044
Well, uh…
Brian, my time is up.

51:29.920 --> 51:30.837
Bye.

51:30.921 --> 51:32.130
Bye.

51:42.099 --> 51:45.852
When Detective McCaffrey went to look
for Anna in court, was she there?

51:45.936 --> 51:46.770
No.

51:46.853 --> 51:49.064
Did she stay to fight her charges?

51:49.147 --> 51:49.981
No.

51:50.065 --> 51:53.860
She went to California because she knew
there was no defense to these charges.

51:53.944 --> 51:57.447
She knew that she was guilty
of these charges.

51:57.531 --> 51:59.366
That shows plainly that the defendant…

51:59.449 --> 52:03.245
White for the closing arguments? Genius.

52:03.328 --> 52:04.996
…committing crimes.

52:05.080 --> 52:07.290
When you go back
to the jury room to deliberate,

52:07.374 --> 52:09.960
I urge you to come to the only verdict

52:10.043 --> 52:12.963
that is in accord
with the law and the evidence.

52:13.046 --> 52:15.048
And that is that the defendant is guilty

52:15.132 --> 52:18.093
beyond a reasonable doubt
of all ten counts.

52:19.928 --> 52:20.762
Thank you.

52:36.069 --> 52:37.362
Mr. Spodek?

52:41.074 --> 52:41.908
Todd.

52:46.872 --> 52:48.748
Remember how I told you I'd kill for you?

52:49.541 --> 52:50.375
What?

52:50.458 --> 52:53.295
Just… trust your costar.

52:53.378 --> 52:54.212
Okay?

52:58.592 --> 53:02.762
You've heard a lot of evidence
from a lot of witnesses in this trial,

53:02.846 --> 53:05.473
but have you noticed one thing throughout?

53:05.557 --> 53:09.394
Every witness who came before you
in this trial was embarrassed.

53:10.478 --> 53:12.355
They didn't want
to tell you the full truth.

53:12.439 --> 53:15.358
Every witness blamed
someone else for their mistakes.

53:15.442 --> 53:16.651
Everyone had a story.

53:17.319 --> 53:20.197
Because every one of them,
all highly paid,

53:20.280 --> 53:23.992
well-educated, experienced businessmen,

53:24.743 --> 53:27.621
every one of them
was fooled by a 25-year-old kid

53:27.704 --> 53:30.081
with no college degree, no credentials,

53:30.165 --> 53:33.293
and no business experience
beyond an internship.

53:33.376 --> 53:35.754
Anna was as green as they come.

53:35.837 --> 53:38.798
In a world where she knew no one
with no idea of what she was doing.

53:38.882 --> 53:43.220
How could she get dangerously close
to fooling these banks?

53:43.303 --> 53:44.512
To getting any of this money?

53:44.596 --> 53:46.765
Now, you may have found Miss Sorokin's

53:46.848 --> 53:50.101
behavior wrong, immoral,
unethical, unorthodox.

53:50.185 --> 53:53.313
You may love her or hate her
for exploiting the system.

53:53.396 --> 53:55.649
-But if anyone in this case…
-What is he--

53:55.732 --> 53:59.194
…is trying to remove people
from their money, it's the bankers.

53:59.277 --> 54:02.155
They will literally do anything
in their nature

54:02.239 --> 54:03.949
to get your accounts and business.

54:04.032 --> 54:06.493
Was Anna ever remotely close

54:06.576 --> 54:08.954
to getting any of these loans
from any of these banks?

54:09.037 --> 54:10.038
Never.

54:10.121 --> 54:13.041
And if she had been,
it wouldn't have gone into her pocket.

54:13.124 --> 54:15.043
It would go to the landlord
for the building

54:15.126 --> 54:16.962
she wanted to renovate for her business.

54:17.045 --> 54:20.966
But look at the evidence, and you'll see,

54:22.467 --> 54:23.969
there was no business.

54:24.052 --> 54:26.888
It was just a dream. An idea.

54:26.972 --> 54:30.308
The only thing that materialized
was a pitch deck.

54:30.392 --> 54:32.602
A few words and pictures.

54:32.686 --> 54:35.563
It was never real. Never tangible.

54:35.647 --> 54:38.483
Anna was young,
ambitious, in over her head,

54:38.566 --> 54:42.487
totally unprepared and incapable
of what she set out to do.

54:42.570 --> 54:44.572
She was never, not for one second close,

54:44.656 --> 54:46.449
let alone dangerously close,

54:46.533 --> 54:49.327
to getting this money
or building this building,

54:49.411 --> 54:52.539
or starting this club,
this art foundation.

54:52.622 --> 54:55.458
It was all talk. Hot air.

54:55.542 --> 55:00.380
A road to nowhere paved
with naiveté and good intentions.

55:01.214 --> 55:03.550
To prove she had the intent,

55:03.633 --> 55:05.885
you'd have to prove
she was dangerously close.

55:05.969 --> 55:09.597
And if you can't find her intent,
you cannot convict her of any crimes.

55:10.849 --> 55:14.102
If you have a reasonable doubt
as to her intent,

55:14.185 --> 55:15.478
her state of mind,

55:15.562 --> 55:19.190
then you must find her not guilty
on all counts.

55:22.944 --> 55:23.820
Thank you.

55:26.323 --> 55:27.574
Thank you, Mr. Spodek.

55:27.657 --> 55:30.243
Now, ladies and gentlemen,
try to stay with me.

55:30.327 --> 55:32.537
I'm going to change the tone
of my voice a little

55:32.620 --> 55:35.749
so that you will pay attention
because this is important.

55:36.541 --> 55:39.085
He tanked her. He totally tanked her.

55:40.837 --> 55:43.298
The indictment
is not evidence of guilt,

55:43.381 --> 55:44.716
it's a notice of the charges…

55:44.799 --> 55:46.885
-I had to. It was…
-…against the defendant

55:46.968 --> 55:50.013
served as the mechanism
for bringing her to trial.

55:50.096 --> 55:52.265
Throughout these proceedings,
the defendant…

55:57.062 --> 55:58.229
Hey.

56:06.654 --> 56:08.114
How long does this shit take?

56:11.034 --> 56:12.494
As long as it takes, I guess.

56:14.245 --> 56:17.332
I'm not a patient person,
so give me some mantra or some shit.

56:20.835 --> 56:24.756
God, give me the strength to accept
the things I cannot change…

56:24.839 --> 56:27.133
You made that up
or steal it from the Bible?

56:30.220 --> 56:31.137
Neither.

56:32.097 --> 56:34.224
My ex is in Alcoholics Anonymous.

57:04.254 --> 57:06.005
So ten counts against Anna, right?

57:06.506 --> 57:08.633
-Yes, Vivian, ten counts.

57:11.136 --> 57:13.596
And she could get 15 years
if convicted on all of them?

57:13.680 --> 57:16.433
You've known this… What is this? Amnesia?

57:16.516 --> 57:18.184
Early onset fucking Alzheimer's--

57:18.268 --> 57:21.062
I'm trying to distract you
so you'll stop twisting that bottle cap.

57:21.146 --> 57:23.314
It's a big hallway, Vivian.

57:29.696 --> 57:33.366
Think it's a one holdout,
<i>12 Angry Men</i> situation in there, or…

57:33.992 --> 57:36.578
Is it the legal definitions
they're struggling with?

57:38.246 --> 57:40.081
I don't even care anymore.

57:40.165 --> 57:41.249
I've done my bit.

57:42.000 --> 57:45.211
I'm getting on a plane for Mexico
in five hours. Come what may.

57:45.837 --> 57:46.671
You're leaving?

57:46.754 --> 57:48.590
Well, it's either that or divorce.

57:48.673 --> 57:49.591
So…

57:50.383 --> 57:52.802
Alexi can handle it from here.
He's more than capable.

57:52.886 --> 57:53.970
You're leaving today?

57:54.554 --> 57:56.556
-It's just a case, Vivian.
-I know that.

57:56.639 --> 57:58.600
I've abandoned my family for long enough.

57:58.683 --> 57:59.767
I get it. It's just…

58:00.935 --> 58:02.562
-Anna's a big girl.
-I know.

58:03.313 --> 58:04.314
It's not that.

58:04.898 --> 58:06.608
It's… I guess…

58:08.151 --> 58:11.237
I don't have the words,
and I should because words are my job,

58:11.321 --> 58:13.323
but the closest thing I can come up with

58:13.406 --> 58:15.366
for how I feel is that I will miss you.

58:18.536 --> 58:21.915
This is not… We'll cross paths.

58:21.998 --> 58:22.832
Of course.

58:22.916 --> 58:25.293
And there'll be other cases of interest.

58:25.376 --> 58:26.753
I mean, for sure.

58:26.836 --> 58:27.670
Right.

58:29.589 --> 58:32.383
We can go out to dinner. The four of us.

58:33.092 --> 58:34.427
Maybe five.

58:35.053 --> 58:37.138
Right. Yeah.

58:40.099 --> 58:40.934
Here's hoping.

58:56.449 --> 58:57.325
Nothing yet?

58:57.408 --> 58:58.576
Don't ask me again.

58:58.660 --> 59:00.828
Maybe there's no connection,
bad service…

59:00.912 --> 59:01.746
Viv's online.

59:01.829 --> 59:03.456
This green light tells me so.

59:03.540 --> 59:06.292
This computer thing
even tells me when she's typing.

59:06.376 --> 59:08.962
It actually tells me
Vivian is typing when she's typing.

59:09.045 --> 59:11.130
Who the fuck needs that much information?

59:11.214 --> 59:14.592
Is that supposed to ease my anxiety?
It does the exact opposite.

59:14.676 --> 59:17.845
Since Vivian's not typing,
I'm making a green tea run. Anybody?

59:18.513 --> 59:19.347
I'm good.

59:19.430 --> 59:21.391
I'll have a… a red eye.

59:21.474 --> 59:22.475
Hold it, hold it…

59:23.393 --> 59:24.644
Vivian is typing.

59:50.503 --> 59:51.337
This is it.

59:51.421 --> 59:52.463
This is it.

59:53.548 --> 59:54.882
Let's bring in the jury.

59:54.966 --> 59:57.760
Everybody, sit down! Now!

1:00:06.352 --> 1:00:08.104
-There's a verdict.
-We can read.

1:00:22.910 --> 1:00:23.745
Hi.

1:00:24.454 --> 1:00:25.705
All right.

1:00:25.788 --> 1:00:26.706
Members of the jury,

1:00:26.789 --> 1:00:30.376
I understand we have a note indicating
you have reached a verdict.

1:00:30.460 --> 1:00:31.628
I would ask the clerk--

1:00:31.711 --> 1:00:33.463
Would the foreperson please stand?

1:00:36.674 --> 1:00:38.009
-You gotta stand up.
-Oh.

1:00:40.303 --> 1:00:41.888
Is the verdict unanimous?

1:00:41.971 --> 1:00:42.889
Yes.

1:00:43.806 --> 1:00:47.101
How say you as to count one,
charging the defendant, Anna Sorokin,

1:00:47.185 --> 1:00:49.646
with attempted grand larceny
in the first degree,

1:00:49.729 --> 1:00:51.898
attempt to steal property
from City National Bank

1:00:51.981 --> 1:00:54.359
exceeding $1 million.
Guilty or not guilty?

1:00:56.486 --> 1:00:57.320
Not guilty.

1:01:02.450 --> 1:01:03.368
Whoo!

1:01:03.451 --> 1:01:05.995
Yeah! Fuck, yeah! Okay.

1:01:06.704 --> 1:01:09.540
How say you as to count two,
charging the defendant

1:01:09.624 --> 1:01:12.460
with attempted grand larceny
in the first degree,

1:01:12.543 --> 1:01:14.962
attempt to steal property
from Fortress Investment Inc.

1:01:15.046 --> 1:01:16.631
exceeding $1 million.

1:01:17.256 --> 1:01:18.466
Guilty or not guilty?

1:01:18.549 --> 1:01:20.843
Come on, come on, come on, type faster.

1:01:20.927 --> 1:01:22.720
Type, Vivian.

1:01:24.472 --> 1:01:25.682
Guilty.

1:01:25.765 --> 1:01:27.475
Count three,
charging the defendant

1:01:27.558 --> 1:01:29.185
with grand larceny in the second degree,

1:01:29.268 --> 1:01:32.605
stolen property
from City National Bank exceeding $50,000.

1:01:32.689 --> 1:01:34.482
-Guilty or not guilty?
-Guilty.

1:01:35.149 --> 1:01:38.611
Count four, charging the defendant
with grand larceny in the second degree,

1:01:38.695 --> 1:01:42.532
stolen property
from Citibank NA exceeding $50,000.

1:01:42.615 --> 1:01:44.909
-Guilty or not guilty?
-Guilty.

1:01:44.992 --> 1:01:48.413
Count five, charging the defendant
with grand larceny in the second degree,

1:01:48.496 --> 1:01:52.375
stolen property
from Rachel Williams exceeding $50,000.

1:01:52.458 --> 1:01:53.668
Guilty or not guilty?

1:01:53.751 --> 1:01:54.961
Not guilty.

1:01:55.044 --> 1:01:58.631
Count six, charging the defendant
with grand larceny in the third degree,

1:01:58.715 --> 1:02:02.260
stolen property
from Signature Bank exceeding $3,000.

1:02:02.343 --> 1:02:04.387
-Guilty or not guilty?
-Guilty.

1:02:04.470 --> 1:02:07.473
Count seven, charging
the defendant with theft of services,

1:02:07.557 --> 1:02:10.810
intent to obtain air transportation
service with Fly Blade Inc.

1:02:10.893 --> 1:02:13.104
-Guilty or not guilty?
-Guilty.

1:02:13.187 --> 1:02:14.272
Beekman Hotel?

1:02:15.022 --> 1:02:15.940
Guilty.

1:02:16.023 --> 1:02:17.859
-W Hotel.
-Guilty.

1:02:17.942 --> 1:02:20.236
-Le Parker Meridien Hotel.
-Guilty.

1:02:33.750 --> 1:02:34.584
Well…

1:02:36.502 --> 1:02:37.587
that's that.

1:02:41.257 --> 1:02:45.178
Ladies and gentlemen,
it has been a very difficult job.

1:02:45.261 --> 1:02:47.555
I understand that and I appreciate it.

1:02:48.431 --> 1:02:51.225
As I said,
no matter what your verdict was,

1:02:51.309 --> 1:02:53.436
you served your community well.

1:02:53.519 --> 1:02:55.271
A couple of things, all of the…

1:02:55.354 --> 1:02:58.858
Hey, we won two out of the three big ones.
That's not nothing.

1:02:59.817 --> 1:03:03.404
-No, yeah. City National and Rachel.
-Mmm-hmm.

1:03:03.488 --> 1:03:04.572
It's not bad.

1:03:05.740 --> 1:03:07.742
If you wish
to speak to them, you may.

1:03:07.825 --> 1:03:11.412
I think that some members of the media
might wish to speak to you as well.

1:03:11.496 --> 1:03:15.458
Again, it is your choice
if you choose to speak with them.

1:03:15.541 --> 1:03:17.919
And I want to mention
something about the media.

1:03:18.002 --> 1:03:20.838
Obviously, you have
seen them here the whole time.

1:03:20.922 --> 1:03:25.218
I'm very proud of the way
you've focused on this case, not on them.

1:03:25.301 --> 1:03:27.428
I'm sorry,
but I've got to go right after this.

1:03:27.512 --> 1:03:29.680
Alexi will walk you through
the next steps.

1:03:29.764 --> 1:03:31.933
I'll be back next week
to check on you. Okay?

1:03:32.600 --> 1:03:33.726
Yes.

1:03:33.810 --> 1:03:35.645
Have a good vacation. You earned it.

1:03:37.814 --> 1:03:40.149
And thanks once again
for your service.

1:03:40.233 --> 1:03:41.108
Thank you.

1:03:42.944 --> 1:03:45.238
You may exit. You are discharged.

1:03:46.572 --> 1:03:49.659
-I'm so proud of you.
-Thank you. That means a lot.

1:03:49.742 --> 1:03:52.078
We should stop and pick up
sticker books for the kiddos

1:03:52.161 --> 1:03:54.288
if you want any chance
of surviving this flight.

1:03:54.372 --> 1:03:55.748
I had Gloria call the hotel

1:03:55.832 --> 1:03:57.875
and sign them up for kids club
every day,

1:03:57.959 --> 1:04:01.170
so we can claim half a day
to ourselves to hit the golf course,

1:04:01.254 --> 1:04:04.006
wander into town,
spend the whole day in bed.

1:04:06.259 --> 1:04:07.093
What is it?

1:04:07.176 --> 1:04:09.512
I can't go. Not now.

1:04:09.595 --> 1:04:11.931
Why? Todd, it's over.

1:04:12.807 --> 1:04:14.725
I'll come as soon as I can.

1:04:17.687 --> 1:04:20.523
I don't think you understand
what you're doing right now.

1:04:21.691 --> 1:04:22.733
I do understand.

1:04:23.818 --> 1:04:25.319
I don't think you understand--

1:04:25.403 --> 1:04:28.322
She's got you parking her car, Todd.
You know that.

1:04:36.622 --> 1:04:37.623
I love you, I…

1:05:11.824 --> 1:05:12.825
You okay?

1:05:13.993 --> 1:05:15.786
You betrayed me.

1:05:17.246 --> 1:05:18.748
That's one way to look at it.

1:05:20.583 --> 1:05:23.210
I also beat two out of three
of your biggest charges.

1:05:23.878 --> 1:05:26.964
You don't have to like how I got there,
but let me explain.

1:05:27.048 --> 1:05:28.132
It doesn't matter.

1:05:29.926 --> 1:05:31.052
It doesn't matter.

1:05:34.096 --> 1:05:36.974
The jury, they saw through you.

1:05:37.058 --> 1:05:42.438
They saw how close
I was to the money, to ADF.

1:05:42.521 --> 1:05:45.650
They saw through Rachel's bullshit.

1:05:45.733 --> 1:05:51.656
I… I didn't need to fuck over
my friends for 60 grand

1:05:51.739 --> 1:05:56.494
when those fucking frat boys at Fortress
were willing to hand over 20 million!

1:05:59.330 --> 1:06:05.044
Those people in there.
They… they saw me.

1:06:05.127 --> 1:06:10.424
I was dangerously close,
and they saw that.

1:06:13.260 --> 1:06:19.475
Now… now the world will know
that I am not an idiot.

1:06:19.558 --> 1:06:22.353
I'm not some dumb socialite.

1:06:27.566 --> 1:06:28.693
I'm a player.

1:06:38.285 --> 1:06:41.831
I was so… I was one step away.

1:06:51.007 --> 1:06:52.383
I'll call your dad.

1:06:53.926 --> 1:06:54.844
I'll let him know.

1:07:03.519 --> 1:07:07.940
The traffic
on your original story is insane.

1:07:08.024 --> 1:07:09.567
Between the trial and sentencing,

1:07:09.650 --> 1:07:11.902
it's consistently peaking
as the top-trending,

1:07:11.986 --> 1:07:14.155
highest read ratio
of any story on the site.

1:07:14.238 --> 1:07:17.074
Globally, over four million
unique impressions.

1:07:17.158 --> 1:07:19.368
We've never seen anything like this.

1:07:19.452 --> 1:07:21.162
-Have we, Paul?
-Not in my memory.

1:07:21.245 --> 1:07:23.372
The interest in this is, well, just…

1:07:24.832 --> 1:07:26.333
We obviously need a follow-up.

1:07:26.417 --> 1:07:27.251
Absolutely.

1:07:27.334 --> 1:07:28.252
Cover story.

1:07:28.335 --> 1:07:29.754
Yeah, big splash.

1:07:29.837 --> 1:07:32.757
Get micro with it.
I want all the inside color.

1:07:32.840 --> 1:07:34.258
The conflict with the judge.

1:07:34.341 --> 1:07:37.678
The whole courtroom,
this runway business.

1:07:37.762 --> 1:07:40.848
Apparently she wore white
on the day of her closing arguments.

1:07:40.931 --> 1:07:42.975
I mean, this chick's amazing.

1:07:43.059 --> 1:07:45.436
Was that white dress her idea?

1:07:45.519 --> 1:07:46.771
Or the stylist's?

1:07:47.521 --> 1:07:48.355
Hey.

1:07:48.981 --> 1:07:49.940
We should move you.

1:07:50.608 --> 1:07:53.527
She needs an office.
The office next to you is free.

1:07:54.153 --> 1:07:55.613
You want the office next to Paul?

1:07:55.696 --> 1:07:57.698
Don't worry about…

1:07:58.741 --> 1:08:01.786
Uh, we're going to need
art directors, photographers…

1:08:06.082 --> 1:08:08.167
-The kid, the Mexican kid.
-Who?

1:08:08.250 --> 1:08:09.085
Oh.

1:08:29.605 --> 1:08:31.690
Landon offered me an office.

1:08:32.942 --> 1:08:33.984
Next to Paul's.

1:08:35.277 --> 1:08:37.154
Attagirl.

1:08:37.238 --> 1:08:38.948
I'm moving out of Scriberia.

1:08:39.031 --> 1:08:41.283
That's the goal.

1:08:47.373 --> 1:08:48.582
Vivian. What?

1:08:50.042 --> 1:08:52.837
It was mine. The white dress Anna wore.

1:08:56.382 --> 1:08:57.842
Huh. Huh.

1:08:57.925 --> 1:09:00.136
I took it out of my closet, Lou.

1:09:02.179 --> 1:09:03.013
Yep.

1:09:05.933 --> 1:09:06.767
Lou…

1:09:07.977 --> 1:09:10.062
Scriberia, white dresses…

1:09:12.857 --> 1:09:15.109
You're burying the lead.

1:09:16.819 --> 1:09:18.487
I care about her.

1:09:19.530 --> 1:09:21.031
More than I should.

1:09:21.907 --> 1:09:23.909
She doesn't care about me at all.

1:09:23.993 --> 1:09:28.122
Did she care about me at all?
Was I just another con?

1:09:30.749 --> 1:09:31.959
The lead.

1:09:32.042 --> 1:09:33.752
Vivian. Huh.

1:09:39.383 --> 1:09:40.759
What the fuck do I do now?

1:09:43.012 --> 1:09:44.805
You move onto the next story.

1:09:47.558 --> 1:09:48.726
That's the job.

1:10:01.906 --> 1:10:04.742
It's okay. It's okay.

1:10:21.675 --> 1:10:24.345
<i>Miss Sorokin,</i>
<i>I have no confidence whatsoever…</i>

1:10:24.428 --> 1:10:28.098
<i>None… Zero… To face the music.</i>

1:10:28.182 --> 1:10:29.934
<i>I am remanding you to Rikers Island</i>

1:10:30.017 --> 1:10:32.895
<i>for five to 15 years,</i>
<i>state prison until trial.</i>

1:10:32.978 --> 1:10:34.438
<i>Anna Sorokin,</i>

1:10:34.521 --> 1:10:38.567
<i>convicted of swindling New York's</i>
<i>elite out of more than $200,000,</i>

1:10:38.651 --> 1:10:41.570
<i>will be sentenced tomorrow</i>
<i>in a Manhattan courtroom.</i>

1:10:41.654 --> 1:10:45.032
<i>Sorokin faces up to 15 years in prison.</i>

1:10:45.741 --> 1:10:47.159
Rachel can write.

1:10:47.243 --> 1:10:49.954
-What's it say? Give it.
-Stop it. You're not in here much.

1:10:50.037 --> 1:10:50.913
Give it!

1:10:51.455 --> 1:10:53.749
Should have come to Morocco,
you'd be famous like me.

1:10:53.832 --> 1:10:55.167
How can she write so fast?

1:10:55.251 --> 1:10:57.211
-She's got the trial in here.
-Give me the book.

1:10:57.294 --> 1:10:58.462
It'll be out by summer.

1:10:58.545 --> 1:11:01.799
You can read it on Jones Beach
like the other basic bitches.

1:11:15.604 --> 1:11:17.273
Here, have at it.

1:11:20.943 --> 1:11:21.944
You know what, no.

1:11:24.113 --> 1:11:27.283
I have wasted enough…

1:11:29.493 --> 1:11:30.911
I'm shooketh.

1:11:32.246 --> 1:11:35.124
I am done… living life
through the eyes of others.

1:11:35.207 --> 1:11:36.875
I am a director.

1:11:36.959 --> 1:11:39.128
I'm a fucking film director, starting now.

1:11:40.254 --> 1:11:43.507
I'm going inside and giving 'em
my two weeks, right now. Watch me.

1:11:44.633 --> 1:11:47.052
-Honey, wait.
-Don't try talking me out of it.

1:11:47.136 --> 1:11:48.929
Wait, Anna's sentence.

1:11:49.013 --> 1:11:50.723
The judge is ruling. It's out.

1:11:51.348 --> 1:11:52.683
How long?

1:12:02.943 --> 1:12:04.194
Twelve years.

1:12:04.987 --> 1:12:05.946
Four to twelve.

1:12:07.281 --> 1:12:10.034
Twelve years.

1:12:10.117 --> 1:12:14.496
In 12 years,
my daughter will have a cellphone.

1:12:14.580 --> 1:12:15.664
Twelve is the max.

1:12:16.957 --> 1:12:19.084
In 12 years,
there won't be Arctic sea ice.

1:12:19.585 --> 1:12:23.005
-I'm not sure what that has to do--
-In 12 years, Anna will be 40.

1:12:23.088 --> 1:12:25.591
She won't be a viral sensation.

1:12:26.967 --> 1:12:28.635
She won't be an Instagram star.

1:12:28.719 --> 1:12:32.264
She won't be daughter of the zeitgeist
or queen of the millennials.

1:12:34.600 --> 1:12:39.772
She'll be a lonely middle-aged woman
whose life was stolen from her.

1:12:44.860 --> 1:12:46.195
Todd.

1:12:46.278 --> 1:12:48.697
What? What do you want me to say?

1:12:49.865 --> 1:12:51.784
You didn't make her do the interview?

1:12:52.743 --> 1:12:53.827
You didn't use her?

1:12:53.911 --> 1:12:55.704
She didn't end up
getting a longer sentence

1:12:55.788 --> 1:12:57.164
because of the media attention?

1:12:57.247 --> 1:13:02.336
Sorry, but you got more clicks,
Anna got more time. Plain and simple.

1:13:05.798 --> 1:13:06.965
How's your phone?

1:13:07.508 --> 1:13:08.384
My phone?

1:13:08.467 --> 1:13:09.635
I'll bet it's ringing.

1:13:10.594 --> 1:13:11.428
Finally.

1:13:11.512 --> 1:13:13.472
Getting some new clients these days?

1:13:13.555 --> 1:13:14.640
Yeah, exactly.

1:13:14.723 --> 1:13:17.393
You're about to get rich
off of this case. Enjoy that.

1:13:17.476 --> 1:13:21.021
Maybe give yourself a break. Regroup.

1:13:21.105 --> 1:13:24.358
-Maybe take your family on vacation--
-I missed my family vacation!

1:13:24.441 --> 1:13:25.859
I suppose that's my fault too?

1:13:25.943 --> 1:13:29.363
Go to the fucking airport.
Be with your family. I'm not stopping you.

1:14:03.313 --> 1:14:04.273
Where's she going?

1:14:05.023 --> 1:14:05.899
Bedford Hills.

1:14:07.067 --> 1:14:08.110
When does she leave?

1:14:34.970 --> 1:14:35.804
Are you nervous?

1:14:36.722 --> 1:14:40.767
Fuck this place. I'm ready for real prison
with real criminal masterminds.

1:14:40.851 --> 1:14:42.728
It'll make the days more interesting.

1:14:42.811 --> 1:14:45.022
And Bedford Hills, they say it's nice.

1:14:45.731 --> 1:14:46.565
Yeah.

1:14:51.320 --> 1:14:55.282
Anna, I… just wanted to say I'm sorry.

1:14:56.408 --> 1:14:57.242
For what?

1:14:58.785 --> 1:15:02.789
For how… everything turned out.

1:15:02.873 --> 1:15:03.999
For all of this.

1:15:04.666 --> 1:15:06.627
-I thought--
-You thought what?

1:15:06.710 --> 1:15:09.379
I know you didn't think
you were going to rescue me.

1:15:10.714 --> 1:15:11.924
Anna, come on.

1:15:12.007 --> 1:15:13.050
No touching.

1:15:16.595 --> 1:15:18.013
I never thought…

1:15:18.096 --> 1:15:20.557
You don't deserve this kind of a sentence.

1:15:20.641 --> 1:15:24.478
The guys who broke the Wall Street banks
didn't get this kind of a sentence.

1:15:24.561 --> 1:15:25.395
You should…

1:15:26.104 --> 1:15:28.065
If I hadn't written that article, I…

1:15:29.024 --> 1:15:31.485
You are just starting out.

1:15:31.568 --> 1:15:34.029
I'm saying… mistakes were made.

1:15:34.112 --> 1:15:38.867
My only mistake was to overestimate
people's ability to handle stress.

1:15:40.911 --> 1:15:42.037
Your only mistake?

1:15:43.580 --> 1:15:48.126
You're telling me… that given
the chance to do this all over again,

1:15:48.210 --> 1:15:49.878
you'd do the exact same things?

1:15:53.715 --> 1:15:54.550
Anna.

1:15:55.467 --> 1:15:58.303
This is it. This is the last time
we're going to see each other.

1:15:58.387 --> 1:16:00.973
I'm saying I'm sorry. I'm asking you--

1:16:01.056 --> 1:16:04.184
No, stop, Vivian. You're not my friend.

1:16:04.268 --> 1:16:08.438
We're not some giggling idiots,
BFF, whatever.

1:16:09.731 --> 1:16:14.319
I don't like you. You have terrible shoes.
This was a transaction. We had a deal.

1:16:15.028 --> 1:16:16.905
-Anna.
-No, it's okay.

1:16:16.989 --> 1:16:19.032
You made good on your part of the deal.

1:16:19.116 --> 1:16:21.952
You said you would
make me famous, and you did.

1:16:22.953 --> 1:16:25.205
Who's more famous right now
than Anna Delvey?

1:16:42.306 --> 1:16:43.307
No touching.

1:16:44.683 --> 1:16:45.767
You'll come visit.

1:16:45.851 --> 1:16:46.727
No touching.

1:16:47.686 --> 1:16:49.021
You'll come visit.

1:16:54.067 --> 1:16:55.027
I'll visit.

1:16:55.110 --> 1:16:56.903
God, just calm the fuck down.

1:16:56.987 --> 1:16:59.489
-Time's up, Anna. Let's go.
-Okay, I got it. Okay.

1:17:06.246 --> 1:17:07.331
Goodbye, Vivian.

1:17:08.749 --> 1:17:09.708
Goodbye, Anna.

1:17:15.881 --> 1:17:16.965
Vivian…

1:17:19.301 --> 1:17:20.260
you look good.

1:17:21.136 --> 1:17:22.220
You lost some weight.

1:17:22.721 --> 1:17:24.139
You're not so fat anymore.
